description: {"blocks":[{"key":"eq5cl","text":"This protocol applies the method by Karst et al. (2021), who used UMI-tagged primers to perform highly accurate long-read amplicon analysis on the full-length ribosomal RNA operons, to the nitrogen fixation (nif) gene cluster. A recent study has shown that the functional gene nifH, which is frequently used in community analysis of diazotrophs, detects many false positives (Mise et al. 2021). Therefore, in this protocol, I used newly developed primers targeting the nifD-K gene (approx. 1.8 kbp) to identify the diazotrophic communities. The present protocol is presented using plant litter and mineral soil as examples, but it could potentially be applied in a variety of environmental samples.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":208,"length":3},{"style":"italic","offset":277,"length":4},{"style":"italic","offset":469,"length":7}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"eo5o3","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"62mrb","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6bfkg","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
